text.paragraph:
Glycopyrrolate oral solution must be measured and administered with an accurate measuring device [see
Patient Counseling Information (17)
].

The presence of high fat food reduces the oral bioavailability of glycopyrrolate oral solution if taken shortly after a meal [see
                     Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)

                    ].

Because glycopyrrolate is largely renally eliminated, glycopyrrolate should be used with caution in patients with renal impairment [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)
]
.
